

Three air passengers were put into police custody at Malaga airport in Spain on Saturday, for one of them joked that he had a bomb on board a plane from Stockholm.

The crew has overheard that one passenger told his friends he had a bomb on board the plane, according to Niels Blix, a spokesman for Sterling Airlines flight.

However, the captain of the flight decided to carry on to Malaga and landed without incident. The Spanish police then detained the three passengers.

